<h2 id="heading-19">Common Automation Mistakes</h2>

<h3 id="heading-20">1. Automating Broken Processes</h3>

<p>Don't automate a messy process. Clean up your bookkeeping first, then automate.</p>

<h3 id="heading-21">2. Over-Automation</h3>

<p>Some things need human judgment. Focus on repetitive, rules-based tasks.</p>

<h3 id="heading-22">3. Ignoring Integration</h3>

<p>Tools that don't talk to each other create more work. Choose integrated solutions.</p>

<h3 id="heading-23">4. No Monitoring</h3>

<p>Automation isn't "set and forget." Monitor for errors and update rules regularly.</p>

